                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client who underwent a hemorrhoidectomy 4 days ago. The client’s last bowel movement was the day before the procedure and the client has been receiving regular stool softeners. Which of the following orders would the nurse anticipate from the primary health care provider?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHemorrhoids are dilated hemorrhoidal veins that result from increased anorectal pressure and weakening of the connective tissue supporting the hemorrhoidal veins. Hemorrhoids can be either internal if the dilated veins are above the internal sphincter or external if the dilated veins are below the external sphincter. Hemorrhoidectomy is used in the treatment of hemorrhoids that cause excessive bleeding, pain, or thrombosis. After the procedure, nursing care focuses on controlling pain and supporting regular bowel habits. Pain control regimens may include an opioid analgesic in combination with a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) in addition to topical medications, such as lidocaine. Stool softeners and bulk-forming laxatives are given to prevent straining with the first defecation after surgery. However, if 2 or 3 days have passed since the client’s last bowel movement, an oil-retention enema is indicated. Therefore, eliminate options 1, 3 and 4 because these are inappropriate interventions given the amount of time that has elapsed since the client’s last bowel movement. Therefore, option 2 is correct.",
                        "id": "32afb367906343ffa4b204d2da2f05c0",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "35855e836274467c99d98980b8a949e2",
                                "content": "I walk 1 to 2 miles every day."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e32ac78096e742aa947262a61ba5f0b6",
                                "content": "I need to decrease fiber in my diet."
