                        "content": "The nurse is assisting a client who had a hemorrhoidectomy 2 days ago with a sitz bath. The client asks the nurse how long the sitz baths are recommended after surgery. What is the appropriate nursing response?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHemorrhoidectomy is surgical excision of hemorrhoids used in the management and treatment of hemorrhoids that are causing certain complications, such as severe bleeding, pain or prolapse. Nursing care after this procedure focuses on pain control and restoring regular bowel habits. Sitz baths are recommended after this procedure to increase comfort and decrease inflammation. Sitz baths are usually performed for 15 to 20 minutes up to 2 or 3 times per day and are continued for 1 to 2 weeks. Eliminate options 1, 3 and 4, as these are all inappropriate time periods. Therefore, option 2 is correct.",
                        "id": "99291c9946154284aa391443203dbf31",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5377cefb259e4a999fbcb25d518f1eac",
                                "content": "“This condition refers to a tear or ulceration in the anal mucosa.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "7222e39488bc4295a0a017cf832f7591",
                                "content": "“This condition refers to a pocket containing pus located in the perianal area.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3b3034af03a94869ac07aa4114379994",
                                "content": "“The condition refers to an abnormal connection or tunnel originating from the anus or rectum.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6c2a0d9c507d46fd98cc221f6e0cf558",
                                "content": "“This condition is best described as a dilated and thrombosed hemorrhoidal vein protruding below the external anal sphincter.”"
