                        "content": "A client diagnosed with an anal fistula asks the nurse to describe this condition. Which of the following is the appropriate nursing response?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAnal fistula refers to an abnormal connection or tunnel originating from the anus or rectum. A common cause of an anal fistula is the rupture of an anorectal abscess. This condition increases the risk of infection if feces enters the fistula. Fistulotomy is used in the treatment of anal fistulas, in which the fistula is opened up, allowing healthy tissue to granulate inside the wound. Option 1 describes an anal fissure. Option 2 describes anorectal abscess. Option 4 describes an external hemorrhoid. Therefore, option 3 is correct, as anal fistula refers to an abnormal connection or tunnel originating from the anus or rectum.",
                        "id": "fc9946a8b5c54e56935073bcb62a8c89",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ebf9a171f3bd450ca92539aef982baf6",
                                "content": "Administer stool softeners as prescribed."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6fb59a9be2594437ba21a911b3292f2e",
                                "content": "Instruct the client to limit fluid intake to avoid urinary retention."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8a6a89443a4f45d4af2486880f9cb0ab",
                                "content": "Encourage a high-fiber diet to promote bowel movements without straining."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3b16675e1b594e3b8861d96c97b5537e",
                                "content": "Apply cold packs to the anal-rectal area over the dressing until the packing is removed."
                            },
                            {
