                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHemorrhoids are dilated hemorrhoidal veins that result from increased anorectal pressure and weakening of the connective tissue supporting the hemorrhoidal veins. Hemorrhoids can be either internal if the dilated veins are above the internal sphincter or external if the dilated veins are below the external sphincter. Risk factors for the development of hemorrhoids include pregnancy, constipation, diarrhea, prolonged sitting or standing, heavy lifting, obesity, straining during defecation, or ascites. Eliminate option 4, as this indicates a normal BMI, whereas obesity is a risk factor for the development of hemorrhoids. Therefore, options 1, 2, 3 and 5 are correct.\n",
